1
00:00:14,584 --> 00:00:20,022
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,856 --> 00:00:28,763
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,831 --> 00:00:34,201
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,270 --> 00:00:38,331
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,575 --> 00:00:44,478
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,214 --> 00:00:52,120
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,522 --> 00:00:57,014
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:57,093 --> 00:01:03,999
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:11,198
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,274 --> 00:01:17,941
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,347 --> 00:01:27,915
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:36,343 --> 00:01:39,972
<i>The Leaf's Handsome Devil!</i>

13
00:01:50,357 --> 00:01:51,790
Blast!

14
00:01:54,394 --> 00:01:55,952
No matter how many times you try...

15
00:01:59,332 --> 00:02:00,390
it's the same!

16
00:02:19,953 --> 00:02:21,443
I'll acknowledge you.

17
00:02:21,888 --> 00:02:24,015
You're not only sharp...

18
00:02:24,291 --> 00:02:26,020
You're also very determined...

19
00:02:28,261 --> 00:02:30,855
In addition, I'm nice, too...

20
00:02:32,365 --> 00:02:37,098
Striking a helpless woman
is against my policy...

21
00:02:37,737 --> 00:02:38,761
But however I look at it,

22
00:02:38,839 --> 00:02:41,740
you don't have the feel of
a helpless woman...

23
00:02:42,943 --> 00:02:44,342
in your case!

24
00:02:52,586 --> 00:02:54,110
Don't be getting full of yourself

25
00:02:54,187 --> 00:02:57,554
just because you released
the Genjutsu, you little clod...!

26
00:02:59,392 --> 00:03:01,383
<i>She's still not completely bound.</i>

27
00:03:01,661 --> 00:03:02,719
<i>Damn it...</i>

28
00:03:04,097 --> 00:03:05,792
<i>I can't lose!</i>

29
00:03:12,005 --> 00:03:13,097
<i>A little more...</i>

30
00:03:33,927 --> 00:03:36,088
<i>What Chakra does she have?!</i>

31
00:03:36,496 --> 00:03:38,123
<i>Even if I bind her</i>
<i>at point blank range,</i>

32
00:03:38,198 --> 00:03:40,029
<i>she still pushes back...</i>

33
00:03:41,201 --> 00:03:44,864
<i>But, I'll get hammered</i>
<i>for sure if I let go now.</i>

34
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:50,176
<i>After all, I just have to put this</i>
<i>to rest with this Jutsu.</i>

35
00:04:18,038 --> 00:04:20,165
<i>Hang in there, Akamaru!</i>

36
00:04:55,275 --> 00:04:58,108
Damn it... What's going on?!

37
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:29,607
Damn it!

38
00:05:44,991 --> 00:05:47,289
One more... to go...

39
00:05:48,862 --> 00:05:51,558
<i>This guy's crazy strong...</i>

40
00:05:53,667 --> 00:05:56,898
<i>Not a single hit with that</i>
<i>many shadow clones...</i>

41
00:05:58,505 --> 00:05:59,767
It's about time...

42
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:02,068
I've been eagerly waiting.

43
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:10,573
Lord Orochimaru's ambition...
The first step...

44
00:06:59,999 --> 00:07:01,261
<i>Sasuke...</i>

45
00:07:07,407 --> 00:07:10,968
Sasuke! What're you doing
with these guys?!

46
00:07:11,878 --> 00:07:14,108
Come on! We're going home now!

47
00:07:19,219 --> 00:07:20,083
Sasuke...

48
00:07:21,121 --> 00:07:22,019
Hey...

49
00:07:34,067 --> 00:07:35,125
<i>Should we go home?</i>

50
00:07:35,568 --> 00:07:36,330
<i>Yeah!</i>

51
00:07:38,204 --> 00:07:41,640
<i>We've both made it to the top!</i>

52
00:07:43,743 --> 00:07:46,337
<i>I want to fight you too.</i>

53
00:07:49,616 --> 00:07:52,084
Hey... We're going home.

54
00:07:55,522 --> 00:07:58,650
Everyone's worried about you.

55
00:08:00,693 --> 00:08:01,853
So...

56
00:08:11,404 --> 00:08:12,962
Sasuke!

57
00:08:13,339 --> 00:08:17,241
<i>Please. Bring back Sasuke...!</i>

58
00:08:18,044 --> 00:08:20,945
You can hear my voice, can't you?!

59
00:08:27,453 --> 00:08:28,943
Wait, Sasuke!

60
00:08:33,259 --> 00:08:34,157
It's futile...

61
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:37,792
Die.

62
00:08:46,406 --> 00:08:47,373
Who're you?

63
00:08:51,444 --> 00:08:52,706
The rejuvenated...

64
00:08:54,147 --> 00:08:56,513
Leaf Village's Handsome Devil...

65
00:09:03,756 --> 00:09:05,053
Rock Lee!

66
00:09:24,835 --> 00:09:26,769
B-Bushy Brow?

67
00:09:31,541 --> 00:09:33,702
Bushy Brow, you!
What about your body...?

68
00:09:34,011 --> 00:09:36,605
More importantly, Naruto.
Go get Sasuke.

69
00:09:38,015 --> 00:09:39,744
But... you...

70
00:09:40,784 --> 00:09:44,049
Please leave this person to me!

71
00:09:48,292 --> 00:09:50,954
<i>This guy's...good...</i>

72
00:09:52,162 --> 00:09:56,861
Bushy Brow! Be careful!
He uses his own bones to attack.

73
00:10:04,274 --> 00:10:07,107
Bones... you say?

74
00:10:09,980 --> 00:10:13,848
He's crazy strong...

75
00:10:23,894 --> 00:10:26,522
What're you doing?!
Please go, quickly!

76
00:10:27,431 --> 00:10:28,420
Naruto...

77
00:10:29,032 --> 00:10:32,729
You also promised Sakura
with a "nice guy pose," right?!

78
00:10:35,839 --> 00:10:38,603
<i>I'll bring back Sasuke, no matter what!</i>

79
00:10:39,042 --> 00:10:41,135
<i>It's a promise of a lifetime!</i>

80
00:10:42,179 --> 00:10:45,046
This person... I'll beat him!

81
00:10:47,284 --> 00:10:48,182
I promise!

82
00:10:51,555 --> 00:10:52,419
Right!

83
00:10:56,927 --> 00:10:57,859
I won't let you!

84
00:11:04,601 --> 00:11:05,590
Die.

85
00:11:09,239 --> 00:11:11,230
Please don't ignore me!

86
00:11:12,642 --> 00:11:13,574
Oh...

87
00:11:17,714 --> 00:11:18,738
<i>Bushy Brow...</i>

88
00:11:19,983 --> 00:11:22,349
You don't have the time
to be inattentive!

89
00:11:25,722 --> 00:11:27,747
<i>Good response!</i>

90
00:11:49,846 --> 00:11:50,744
However...

91
00:11:51,715 --> 00:11:54,843
If Sasuke is inside that coffin...

92
00:11:56,086 --> 00:12:00,750
It'd be totally impossible to take them
on with a Genin team...

93
00:12:01,825 --> 00:12:04,919
We Jonin are in this plight...

94
00:12:06,029 --> 00:12:10,557
We should organize a special team
and send them out for backup.

95
00:12:11,234 --> 00:12:12,394
We can't do that...

96
00:12:14,304 --> 00:12:16,499
Ever since Orochimaru's attack,

97
00:12:16,807 --> 00:12:20,436
the Leaf is currently losing strength
as a great land.

98
00:12:21,945 --> 00:12:24,937
You understand that the Jonin
and Chunin are being totally mobilized

99
00:12:25,015 --> 00:12:28,416
in order to take out possible domestic
and international dangers.

100
00:12:32,889 --> 00:12:36,950
Even if the Sharingan were to fall
into Orochimaru's hands...

101
00:12:39,896 --> 00:12:43,798
We should now prioritize
avoiding war with other lands.

102
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:50,331
But... I'm sure the Orochimaru situation
isn't a problem that can be deferred forever.

103
00:12:50,707 --> 00:12:54,803
If he regains power...
He'll promptly attack again...

104
00:12:55,312 --> 00:12:56,279
I know...

105
00:12:57,214 --> 00:13:00,274
I'm not such a fool.

106
00:13:02,118 --> 00:13:05,349
I was sure to think about it and
measures have already been taken.

107
00:13:09,860 --> 00:13:10,758
In here!

108
00:13:20,103 --> 00:13:22,264
What's wrong, Guy?
You're on the brink of exhaustion.

109
00:13:22,839 --> 00:13:24,204
Did something happen
on your mission?

110
00:13:24,274 --> 00:13:29,610
No... I took care of the mission
and ran back with all of my might...

111
00:13:31,948 --> 00:13:33,779
More importantly...

112
00:13:34,951 --> 00:13:39,684
Lee! What happened with
Lee's surgeny?!

113
00:13:45,428 --> 00:13:46,656
It was a success.

114
00:13:48,431 --> 00:13:52,128
He can start training starting tomorrow
if it's just for Jutsu.

115
00:13:56,573 --> 00:14:00,976
Well, bed rest for a while
would be best though.

116
00:14:01,411 --> 00:14:03,572
Th-There's trouble, Lady Fifth Hokage.

117
00:14:04,247 --> 00:14:07,011
Rock Lee is gone!

118
00:14:10,887 --> 00:14:14,015
No!

119
00:14:42,152 --> 00:14:45,053
Next will be the end.

120
00:14:54,431 --> 00:14:59,027
Damn it... Last night while
I treated Genma and Raido?

121
00:15:01,605 --> 00:15:02,594
<i>Lee...</i>

122
00:15:07,744 --> 00:15:11,271
That fool... He went after them.

123
00:15:16,286 --> 00:15:19,483
And... he must've been really flustered...

124
00:15:26,196 --> 00:15:30,428
He took my bottle of sake for
a bottle of medicine by mistake...

125
00:15:31,768 --> 00:15:36,831
SAKE

126
00:15:46,216 --> 00:15:47,615
<i>Sake?!</i>

127
00:15:50,987 --> 00:15:52,454
<i>Uh...Uh oh...</i>

128
00:15:54,524 --> 00:15:55,821
What's wrong, Guy?

129
00:15:58,628 --> 00:16:02,997
Actually, when Lee drinks even
a little bit of alcohol...

130
00:16:09,339 --> 00:16:13,070
Things get... so messy...

131
00:16:13,743 --> 00:16:15,438
Get so messy?

132
00:16:16,946 --> 00:16:19,574
Severe Leaf Hurricane!

133
00:16:39,069 --> 00:16:42,402
<i>He's agile... My kicks don't hit.</i>

134
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,301
You're flexible to
a surprising extent...

135
00:16:45,375 --> 00:16:48,003
And you make unique movements, eh?

136
00:16:49,312 --> 00:16:52,907
You're too... straight forward.

137
00:17:00,423 --> 00:17:01,515
It's over...

138
00:17:03,226 --> 00:17:04,488
Please wait!

139
00:17:14,637 --> 00:17:18,038
I'm sorry.
It's about time for my medicine!

140
00:17:18,308 --> 00:17:20,105
I have to be sure to drink it, so...

141
00:17:20,376 --> 00:17:21,274
Excuse me a moment.

142
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:34,117
I've always disliked medicine.

143
00:17:39,529 --> 00:17:44,091
It... happened before when
I took him to a restaurant

144
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:46,465
to celebrate his acquisition
of the "Hidden Lotus"

145
00:17:47,971 --> 00:17:50,997
Lee mistook my sake for water...

146
00:17:54,177 --> 00:17:56,941
As soon as he drank just
a small cup...

147
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:03,777
of the sake, things got ugly...

148
00:18:03,953 --> 00:18:05,284
Got ugly...?

149
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:13,290
After a silence that was like
right before a storm...

150
00:18:20,937 --> 00:18:22,871
The moment I realized it,

151
00:18:23,807 --> 00:18:24,739
the restaurant...

152
00:18:26,943 --> 00:18:28,774
had gotten all messed up...

153
00:18:32,015 --> 00:18:35,007
Medicine always tastes stran...

154
00:18:47,030 --> 00:18:51,023
<i>What...? What did this guy drink?</i>

155
00:18:54,337 --> 00:18:57,033
Messed up?
What do you mean?

156
00:18:57,907 --> 00:19:01,206
He's terribly...!

157
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:05,841
Lady Tsunade... Lee goes into

158
00:19:08,651 --> 00:19:11,620
an incredible drunken frenzy!

159
00:19:12,522 --> 00:19:13,318
Huh?

160
00:19:23,433 --> 00:19:26,630
Who the heck are you?! Hey!

161
00:19:27,036 --> 00:19:30,005
Geez, who are you anyway?

162
00:19:30,173 --> 00:19:33,074
Acting cool... So irritating...

163
00:19:35,812 --> 00:19:39,680
Hence, he's a natural user of...

164
00:19:55,465 --> 00:19:57,797
Drunken Fist!

165
00:20:56,826 --> 00:20:58,088
Sasuke!

166
00:21:12,142 --> 00:21:14,542
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

167
00:21:14,611 --> 00:21:17,637
<i>And you smiled</i>

168
00:21:17,881 --> 00:21:20,076
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

169
00:21:20,150 --> 00:21:22,983
<i>In my own words</i>

170
00:21:23,053 --> 00:21:28,616
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

171
00:21:28,725 --> 00:21:34,163
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

172
00:21:34,331 --> 00:21:39,826
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

173
00:21:39,936 --> 00:21:45,568
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

174
00:21:46,376 --> 00:21:51,746
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

175
00:21:52,015 --> 00:21:58,818
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

176
00:21:59,222 --> 00:22:02,020
<i>I feel so sad</i>

177
00:22:02,092 --> 00:22:02,990
<i>But...</i>

178
00:22:03,059 --> 00:22:05,289
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

179
00:22:05,362 --> 00:22:08,559
<i>And you smiled</i>

180
00:22:08,632 --> 00:22:10,964
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

181
00:22:11,034 --> 00:22:14,299
<i>In my own words</i>

182
00:22:14,371 --> 00:22:16,601
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

183
00:22:16,673 --> 00:22:20,006
<i>And you smiled</i>

184
00:22:20,076 --> 00:22:22,408
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

185
00:22:22,479 --> 00:22:25,414
<i>In my own words</i>

186
00:22:25,482 --> 00:22:30,146
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

187
00:22:38,662 --> 00:22:40,129
You fell for it, didn't you?!

188
00:22:40,196 --> 00:22:41,891
How about my strategy?

189
00:22:42,065 --> 00:22:44,898
This is the Shinobi Secret
of reading the double bluff!

190
00:22:44,968 --> 00:22:49,098
Guy Sensei! I did it once again!
Yeah!

191
00:22:49,172 --> 00:22:52,767
But, what's this?!
The world is oddly...

192
00:22:52,976 --> 00:22:58,243
f-floating,
and I've no inclination of losing!

193
00:22:58,648 --> 00:23:02,641
Next episode: "The Beast Within.
